Project: M1 Meghalaya Portal
Client: Government of Meghalaya
Role: Full Stack Developer

I have worked on many projects, but currently, I am working on the M1 Meghalaya Portal for the Government of Meghalaya.

Project Overview:

The project consists of two main portals:

Citizen Portal
Department Portal
Objective:

The main goal of this project is to provide a single-window solution for both citizens and government officers:

For Citizens: Access various government schemes and services.
For Officers: Efficiently manage daily operations, file creation, and financial approvals.
Key Features:
Citizen Signup: Citizens can sign up using Ration Card or Voter ID and apply for different schemes.
Scheme Flow: Each scheme has a different process flow, and files are sent to various government officers at different levels for approval.
Hierarchical Approval: The portal supports different levels of officers who handle approvals based on the scheme or file.
Dashboard & Reports: Created dashboards for monitoring and managing workflows. Generated detailed reports for officers.
Large Data Handling: Optimized the system to handle large amounts of data efficiently.

